Preheat oven to 180C/350F/Gas 4.Melt the butter in a saucepan and add the spinach. Cook for about one minute until the spinach has just wilted.Lay the buttered spinach in the base of a small ovenproof dish.Crack in the two eggs and season, to taste, with salt and freshly ground black pepper.Add the cream and sprinkle evenly with the cheddar.Bake in the oven for 6-8 minutes, or until the eggs have set and the top is golden-brown and bubbling.